<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 543/97 of 17 March 1997 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 on the granting of aids for transport by rail, road and inland waterway </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 543/97, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 toetuste andmise kohta raudtee-, maantee- ja siseveetranspordile 17. m&auml;rts 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Articles 75 and 94 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikleid 75 ja 94, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure referred to in Article 189c of the Treaty (3), </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 189c s&auml;testatud korras (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas Council Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 of 4 June 1970 on the granting of aids for transport by rail, road and inland waterway (4), provides the Member States with the possibility of developing combined transport by the granting of aid relating to investments in infrastructure, in fixed and mobile equipment necessary for transhipment and in transport equipment specifically geared to combined transport and used only in combined transport or aid concerning the running costs of an intra-Community combined transport service transiting through the territory of third countries; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) n&otilde;ukogu 4. juuni 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 (4) (toetuste andmise kohta raudtee-, maantee- ja siseveetranspordile) antakse liikmesriikidele v&otilde;imalus kombineeritud transpordi arendamiseks toetuste abil, mida antakse investeeringute tegemiseks infrastruktuuridesse, &uuml;mberlaadimiseks vajalikesse p&uuml;si- ja liikuvseadmetesse ja kombineeritud transpordi jaoks spetsiaalselt kohandatud v&otilde;i ainult seal kasutatavatesse transpordiseadmetesse, ning toetuste abil kolmandaid riike l&auml;biva &uuml;hendusesisese kombineeritud transporditeenuse jooksvate kulude katteks; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the growing requirement for mobility is placing ever increasing demands and pressures on people and the environment; whereas, to take account of the present highly uneven spread of costs and pressures between the different modes of transport, the possibility must be created of support for environment-friendly forms of transport; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) kasvav vajadus mobiilsuse j&auml;rele avaldab inimestele ja keskkonnale j&auml;rjest suuremat survet ning seab nende ette uusi n&otilde;udmisi; v&otilde;tmaks arvesse praegust kulude ja n&otilde;udmiste eba&uuml;htlast jaotumist eri transpordiliikide vahel tuleb luua v&otilde;imalus keskkonnas&otilde;bralike transpordiliikide toetamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas the current overall transport policy has not yet succeeded in creating the conditions for healthy competition between the various modes of transport; whereas no financial equilibrium has yet been achieved within the railway companies; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) praeguse &uuml;ldise transpordipoliitika abil ei ole veel suudetud tekitada eri transpordiliikide vahel ausat konkurentsi; raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate seas ei ole veel saavutatud finantstasakaalu; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas the development of combined transport reveals that the launching phase of this technique has not yet been completed in all regions of the Community; whereas the aid arrangements have accordingly to be extended; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) kombineeritud transpordi arendamine n&auml;itab, et k&otilde;nealuse meetodi k&auml;ivitusetapp ei ole &uuml;henduse k&otilde;igis piirkondades veel l&otilde;ppenud; seep&auml;rast tuleks toetuste andmise aega pikendada; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas, consequently, it is appropriate to maintain current aid arrangements in force until 31 December 1997; whereas the Council should take a decision, under the conditions provided for in the Treaty, on the arrangements to be applied thereafter or, if necessary, on the conditions under which these aids should cease; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) j&auml;relikult on asjakohane j&auml;tta praegu kehtiv toetuste andmise kord j&otilde;usse 31.detsembrini 1997; n&otilde;ukogu peaks tegema vastavalt asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud tingimustele otsuse p&auml;rast seda kuup&auml;eva kohaldatava korra kohta ja vajaduse korral toetuste l&otilde;petamise tingimuste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas the possibility of granting aid for the running costs of combined transport services transiting through the territory of third countries has to be maintained only for Switzerland and the States of former Yugoslavia; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) v&otilde;imalus anda toetust kolmandaid riike l&auml;biva &uuml;hendusesisese kombineeritud transporditeenuse jooksvate kulude katteks tuleb s&auml;ilitada ainult &Scaron;veitsi ja endise Jugoslaavia riikide puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas Decision 75/327/EEC (5), to which Article 4 of Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 refers, was repealed by Article 13 of Directive 91/440/EEC of 29 July 1991 on the development of the Community's railways (6); whereas Article 4 should therefore be deleted; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) otsus 75/327/EM&Uuml;, (5) millele osutatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse 1107/70 artiklis 4, on tunnistatud kehtetuks direktiivi 91/440/EM&Uuml; (6) (&uuml;henduse raudteede arendamise kohta) artikliga 13; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks artikkel 4 kehtetuks tunnistada; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas the categories of aid authorized for combined transport have been shown to operate satisfactorily and that it is possible, consequently, to simplify checks on these by exempting them from the procedure referred to in Article 93 (3) of the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) kombineeritud transpordi puhul lubatud toetuste liigid on toiminud rahuldavalt ning seet&otilde;ttu on v&otilde;imalik lihtsustada nende kontrollimist ja loobuda nende suhtes asutamislepingu artikli 93 l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud korra kohaldamisest; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the laying down of rules relating to aids allocated by Member States for transport is a matter of exclusive Community competence and must take the form of a regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) liikmesriikide poolt transpordile antavaid toetusi k&auml;sitlevate eeskirjade s&auml;testamine kuulub &uuml;henduse ainup&auml;devusse ja seda tuleb teha m&auml;&auml;ruse vormis; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas it is appropriate to amend Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 accordingly, </inglise>
<eesti> 10) seet&otilde;ttu on kohane muuta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
